hands_on_practices.problem:
Consider a $3 \times 3$ real matrix $A$ that is upper triangular and non-diagonal. The entries on the main diagonal of $A$ are specified as $a_{11} = 1$, $a_{22} = 2$, and $a_{33} = 3$. The matrix $A$ also satisfies the following conditions related to its eigenvectors:
\begin{itemize}
    \item An eigenvector corresponding to the eigenvalue $\lambda_2 = 2$ is $v_2 = \begin{pmatrix} 4 \\ 1 \\ 0 \end{pmatrix}$.
    \item An eigenvector corresponding to the eigenvalue $\lambda_3 = 3$ is $v_3 = \begin{pmatrix} 7 \\ 2 \\ 1 \end{pmatrix}$.
\end{itemize}
Given these properties, calculate the entry in the first row and third column of the matrix $A^2$.
